04436nam a22007095i 9783110981254DE-B159720240306014423.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20232023gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2023939211  a97831109812547 a10.1515/97831109812542doi  a(DE-B1597)627623  a(OCoLC)1395182959  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE  aBC 6610qSEPA2rvk0(DE-625)rvk/9536:1 aDayfani, Hila, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Transmission of the Pentateuch :bAnalysis of Variants Due to Graphic Similarity between MT and SP /cHila Dayfani. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2023] 4c©2023  a1 online resource (X, 224 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aStudia Samaritana ;v1300tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgments -- t1 Introduction -- t2 The Textual Evidence -- t3 The Paleographic Background of the Textual Evidence -- t4 Conclusions and Implications -- tAppendix -- tBibliography -- tIndex of Biblical References -- tIndex of Modern Authors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe volume focuses on variants between the Masoretic Text and the Samaritan Pentateuch promptedby graphic similarities between letters. As a phenomenon that occurs during the transmission of ancient texts, an in-depth study of the linguistic and paleographic background of these variants provides fruitful ground for the exploration of the Pentateuch transmission.This volume gathers all the relevant variants from the Masoretic Text and the Samaritan Pentateuch, comparing them to further witnesses, primarily the Dead Sea Scrolls and the Septuagint. Each case is examined independently through a linguistic analysis of the variants, their process of development and an evaluation of which version is preferable (when possible). It then presents a statistical analysis of the data.Moreover, the volume offers a paleographic analysis of the interchanging letters in the three relevant scripts – Hebrew, Jewish, and Samaritan script. Through this process it determines the script in which the variants have occurred and estimates the chronological framework of the variants.This study has implications for the textual history of the Samaritan Pentateuch and, more broadly, for the distribution of the Pentateuch and the extent of its transmission in the late Second Temple period.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024)  aLinguistics.  aMasoretic Text.  aPaleography.  aSamaritan Pentateuch.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishz978311131928508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831109813600 cprintz978311079804340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311098125440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110981254423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110981254/original  a978-3-11-131928-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023